Exception Handling: try-catch

try  // contains the code that might throw an exception
{
 .  //IOException
 .  //SQLException
 .  //ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

}
catch(IOException e)// handles the exception if occurs
{


}

catch(SQLException e)// handles the exception if occurs
{


}
catch(ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e)// handles the exception if occurs
{


}
catch(Exception e)// handles the exception if occurs
{


}

Exception Types:
Checked: Checked at compile time. Must be handled using try-catch or throws.
Unchecked: Occur at runtime. Not mandatory to handle.




throw and throws:

throw new ArithmeticException("Exception occurred");

method - contains checked exception - comiler will force the programmer 
to handle it

i)try-catch
ii)throws

i)When you don't want to handle the exception in the current method
ii)When you want to pass the responsibility to the caller

Java 7: try with resource
Java 9: try with resources

